fm: int minSteps(int n) {         if (n == 1)             return 0;         vector<int> dp(n + 1, INT_MAX);         dp[1] = 0;         dp[2] = 2;         for (int i = 3; i <= n; ++i)             for (int j = 1; j < i; ++j)                 if (i % j == 0)                     dp[i] = min(dp[i], dp[j] + i / j);         return dp[n];     }

bool findTarget(TreeNode *root, int k) {         if (!root)             return false;         unordered_set<int> num;         queue<TreeNode *> val;         val.push(root);         while (!val.empty()) {             TreeNode *temp = val.front();             int &&tempNum = k - temp->val;             if (num.find(tempNum) != num.end())                 return true;             else                 num.insert(temp->val);             val.pop();             if (temp->left) val.push(temp->left);             if (temp->right) val.push(temp->right);         }         return false;     }

fc: class Solution { public:     TreeNode *constructMaximumBinaryTree(vector<int> &nums) {         return Traverse(nums, 0, nums.size());     }      TreeNode *Traverse(vector<int> &nums, int &&i, int &&j) {         if (i >= j)             return nullptr;         auto maxNum = max_element(nums.begin() + i, nums.begin() + j);         int maxI = distance(nums.begin(), maxNum);         TreeNode *curr = new TreeNode(*maxNum);         curr->left = Traverse(nums, i + 0, maxI + 0);         curr->right = Traverse(nums, maxI + 1, j + 0);         return curr;     } };
